Checking in sometimes requires showing up and allowing space for the person to feel and be seen. Whether it’s to cry, laugh, vent, or sit in silence. 

& I know it’s hard but try not to hide when you’re not feeling your best. You deserve love at the ugly stages too! Reach out and tell someone you love that you need them. 

My heart breaks for those losing the battle to mental health. Idgaf what social media makes to think of yourself, YOU ARE NOT ALONE!! 

Transparency: I was actually depressed in this video and my sister showing up for me helped tremendously. I’ve battled depression since my teens and do a damn good job of masking it so please just show up for someone if they’re telling you they’re not ok. And if no one else tells you….
 I LOVE YOU AND YOU ARE NEEDED IN THIS WORLD❤️

#mentalhealth #askforhelp #suicideprevention

I spent 2022 trying to go back to work, save money and move states. Not gone lie, I felt ashamed and like I had failed. But I needed a reset after the pandemic and I was determined to make a fresh start for myself. From a different perspective, I’m grateful to have multiple ways to earn money and I’m not ashamed (I’m really a badass!). Yes, I loveeee to entertain/create and want to go full time but in the meantime THANK YOU GOD FOR PROVIDING.
•
•
So if you’re an artist/creator please show yourself grace. If you had to go back to work, move in with your parents, take a break and/or switch professions completed. You are worthy at every stage❤️

HEY NEW (and old) FOLLOWERS! Thanks for following and supporting me in all my seasons. I am a creator who loves bringing joy and light to ppl. Lately, I’ve struggled to find that light for myself. Letting expectations and judgement of others  dictate what I post and how I move. Instagram become low key depressing and so strategic, I grew tired of playing the trend and algorithm game.  I just want to be free and do what brings me joy, whatever that looks like. Idk if I want to be a comedian (it just happened by me being myself) and that’s ok. Idk where this journey is taking me and that’s ok too. 

I’m posting this to hold myself accountable. To not dim my light trying to figure out a master plan. I am trusting that God has great things in store and I’m opening myself to that. I’m not waiting to get the perfect idea or the perfect connections. My mind is a beautiful and chaotic place that I want to share and not overthink. So welcome to chaos lol, a more authentic version of who I am. Everyday will look different and that’s ok. I love the way y’all love me and I’m grateful for the support❤️

Apologize to me NOW!

Some relationships are worth fighting for… people that try their best, that admit their wrongs (in due time lol), that love you at your worst, that don’t leave you when you can’t do for them. This new era of “cut them off” gives me running from growth and being challenged. Family will test tf outta you and demand you be real with yourself and with them. It comes with heart break and disappointment but it also comes with having ppl to have your back no matter what. & Trust me, sometimes YOU ARE THE PROBLEM.

I often joked about how 2023 beat my ass but there were so many highlights when I shift my perspective.

-I planned a family park day with all my siblings and nieces and nephews. I was beautiful and so healing. 

-Got to bond closer with my sister who’s been in Atlanta 10+ yrs 

-made genuine connections in Atlanta with beautiful women 

-Surprised my mom for Mothers Day 

-Bahamas with my best girl👯‍♀️ 

-Flew my nieces out on their first flight and had A TIME

-Visited DC and connected with old friends who treated me like royalty 🥹

-Was not feeling the Christmas spirit so I threw a party and it was sooo much fun filled with so much laughing and love
